@volatyl3 @Traveling_89 @TehminaKaoosji Studies demonstrate that if you had Omicron (BA.1 or BA.1.1), then you are unlikely to get reinfected with BA.2.

Does it happen, yes, but rarely and symptoms are attenuated.

https://t.co/RNqs0N4pbe

@volatyl3 @Traveling_89 @TehminaKaoosji In studies, the attached included, the odds of being hospitalized after a BA.2 infection did NOT differ from infection with BA.1 (omicron).

Additionally, if hospitalized, the odds of severe disease did not differ for individuals with BA.2 from BA.1

https://t.co/FGfybJUHUy
